Odd-level SU(2) simple-current orbit GKS diagnostics
Date: 2026-07-22 UTC

Build
-----
$ make -B -j1 search_su2_odd_orbit_gks
g++ -O2 -std=c++20 -Wall -Wextra -Wpedantic -Wconversion \
    -Wsign-conversion -Wshadow -Werror \
    search_su2_odd_orbit_gks.cpp -o search_su2_odd_orbit_gks

1. Independent odd-cyclic Monge identity
-----------------------------------------
$ ./search_su2_odd_orbit_gks cyclic-check 6 8
...
progress rank=6 level=11 factors=8 degree_words=5890 \
    cumulative_words=13073 boundary_entries=78438 cyclic_entries=78438
SU2_ODD_ORBIT_GKS ranks=2..6 maximum_factors=8 words=17717 \
    corner_entries=17717 boundary_entries=100484 zero_corners=8465 \
    zero_boundary_entries=9028 cyclic_entries=100484 \
    minimum_corner=0@target0:[+1] \
    minimum_positive_corner=1@target0:[] \
    minimum_boundary=0@target1:[] \
    minimum_positive_boundary=1@target0:[] result=PASS

The orbit calculation uses the folded SU(2) fusion rule.  Independently,
the cyclic calculation relabels each orbit by its even lift, evolves the
Laurent coefficient array on C_(2m+1) x C_(2m+1) by signed interval
convolution, and extracts the adjacent Monge difference

  P_hat(c,0)-P_hat(c,1)-P_hat(c+1,0)+P_hat(c+1,1).

All 100,484 compared partial-character coefficients agree exactly.

2. Symbolic cyclic outer-Turan telescope
----------------------------------------
$ ./search_su2_odd_orbit_gks turan-check 100
SU2_ODD_ORBIT_TURAN ranks=2..100 identities=9900 result=PASS

For both possible exchange parities and every radius at each tested rank,
this constructs the complete local interval feature string as an exact
integer quadratic form in the remainder charges.  It agrees term by term
with

  2[(b_a^2-b_(a-1)b_(a+1))
    -(b_(a+1)^2-b_a b_(a+2))],

including the cyclic antipodal convention at a=m-1.

3. Extended support-disjoint signed-word search
------------------------------------------------
$ /usr/bin/time -f 'elapsed=%e maxrss=%MKB' \
    ./search_su2_odd_orbit_gks 8 12
...
progress rank=8 level=15 factors=12 degree_words=596610 \
    cumulative_words=1392065 boundary_entries=11136520
SU2_ODD_ORBIT_GKS ranks=2..8 maximum_factors=12 words=1866279 \
    corner_entries=1866279 boundary_entries=14328179 \
    zero_corners=917181 zero_boundary_entries=921295 \
    minimum_corner=0@target0:[+1] \
    minimum_positive_corner=1@target0:[] \
    minimum_boundary=0@target1:[] \
    minimum_positive_boundary=1@target0:[] result=PASS
elapsed=74.22 maxrss=3072KB

For each orbit label, the exhaustive enumeration uses multiplicity zero or
a positive multiplicity carrying one common sign.  This is precisely the
support-disjoint chamber supplied by Proposition 5.  The corner entries are
the GKS2* inequalities.  Testing every target is the stronger
partial-character positivity statement equivalent to the full
simple-current boundary column.  These bounded PASS results are evidence,
not a uniform proof.

