The analyzer first verifies the exact rank-three fusion relation
A_2=A_1^2-A_1-I.  The plus matrices U,Q preserve the standard symmetric-
square orthant.  Each paired-minus matrix P,R,T has negative entries, so
that standard orthant is not a common invariant cone.  Proposition 22H3N
instead proves positivity by dominance among the three unordered spectral
pairs.
